From: Michael Massee <michael.massee@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] tdf#XXXXXX vcl: seed initial color in UNO ColorPicker

The com.sun.star.cui.ColorPicker / com.sun.star.ui.dialogs.ColorPicker
service stores an initial color via setPropertyValues("Color", ...) into
m_aColor, but ColorPicker::execute() never propagates that value to the
ColorDialog instance. As a result, the picker always opens with the
default color, regardless of what the caller set.

The pre-2025-06 implementation in cui/source/dialogs/colorpicker.cxx did
pass mnColor to ColorPickerDialog's constructor:

    std::unique_ptr<ColorPickerDialog> xDlg(new ColorPickerDialog(
        Application::GetFrameWeld(mxParent), mnColor, mnMode));

The reintroduction in commit 9d6ade1f3b8e (Nov 2025) and the subsequent
refactor in commit 86a04e193376 / cbfae1c3be2d (Dec 2025) lost that
behavior.

Fix: call ColorDialog::SetColor(m_aColor) before Execute().

This restores parity with the pre-drop implementation and makes the
service usable for non-trivial callers (e.g. extensions that need to
edit an existing color).

---
 vcl/source/components/ColorPicker.cxx | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/vcl/source/components/ColorPicker.cxx b/vcl/source/components/ColorPicker.cxx
index 4ddba4fed433..xxxxxxxxxxxx 100644
--- a/vcl/source/components/ColorPicker.cxx
+++ b/vcl/source/components/ColorPicker.cxx
@@ -105,6 +105,7 @@ void SAL_CALL ColorPicker::setTitle(const OUString&) {}
 sal_Int16 SAL_CALL ColorPicker::execute()
 {
     ColorDialog aColorDialog(Application::GetFrameWeld(m_xParent));
+    aColorDialog.SetColor(m_aColor);
     const int nRet = aColorDialog.Execute();
     if (nRet == RET_OK)
         m_aColor = aColorDialog.GetColor();
--
